As a Database Operations Manager, the responsibilities include:

Strategically provisioning databases and devising appropriate high availability/disaster recovery (HA/DR) solutions aligned with the business division's Recovery Time Objective (RTO) and Recovery Point Objective (RPO).
Overseeing the configuration, maintenance, and troubleshooting of critical database technologies such as log shipping, database mirroring, Always-On Availability Groups, and SQL Server Failover Cluster, ensuring seamless operation across single and multiple subnets.
Leading performance tuning initiatives, addressing complex issues spanning query optimization, index efficiency, TempDB management, IO optimization, high CPU usage, and synchronization challenges in high availability environments.
Managing the setup and configuration of SQL Server Clusters to guarantee system stability and resilience.
Orchestrating weekly patching routines for both standalone and clustered instances to uphold security and performance standards.
Spearheading migration and upgrade projects, orchestrating smooth transitions from legacy SQL Server versions to modern iterations (2016-2019).
Directing the development and support of Extract, Transform, Load (ETL) processes, facilitating seamless data flow from diverse sources like Oracle, Sybase, Access, and Excel into SQL Server.
Ensuring the integrity of database permissions and security settings to safeguard sensitive information.
Supervising the execution of daily, weekly, monthly, and quarterly maintenance tasks, promptly resolving any encountered issues.
Driving automation initiatives through PowerShell scripting to streamline repetitive tasks and enhance operational efficiency.
Conducting comprehensive health checks on extensive server estates using scripted solutions to proactively identify and mitigate potential performance bottlenecks.
Addressing database space constraints, mitigating excessive log growth, and implementing normalization techniques to optimize database structures.
Collaborating closely with cross-functional teams to implement server, instance, and database changes in alignment with organizational objectives.
Providing dedicated support and guidance to application owners and developers, ensuring seamless database operations and performance.



Responsibilities

•	Oversee all aspects of database administration including installation, configuration, maintenance, performance tuning, capacity planning, and security.

•	Implement and manage high availability and disaster recovery solutions such as log shipping, Always-On Availability Groups, and SQL Server Failover Cluster.

•	Proactively identify and resolve performance issues through query optimization, index tuning, resource utilization analysis, and database schema refinement.

•	Automated and Deployed Scripts for database backup and implemented backup and recovery strategies to ensure data integrity and minimize downtime in case of system failures or disasters.

•	database security by implementing access controls, encryption, and auditing mechanisms to protect sensitive data from unauthorized access or breaches.

•	Develop automation scripts using PowerShell or other scripting languages to streamline routine administrative tasks, improve efficiency, and reduce manual intervention.

•	Monitor database growth trends and plan for future capacity requirements by analyzing resource utilization, performance metrics, and business needs.

•	Database Upgrades and Migrations: Plan and execute database upgrades, migrations, and version transitions while minimizing disruption to ongoing operations.

•	Documentation and Knowledge Sharing: Maintain comprehensive documentation of database configurations, procedures, and troubleshooting guides. Share knowledge and best practices with team members to enhance overall expertise and efficiency.

•	Collaboration and Support: Collaborate with cross-functional teams including developers, network engineers, and system administrators to support application development, deployment, and infrastructure initiatives.

Achievements:

•	Led cost reduction initiative which help save over $2 million on SQL Server License Cost.
•	Successfully implemented a high availability solution using SQL Server Always-On Availability Groups, reducing downtime and improving system reliability by 99.9%.

•	Optimized database performance through proactive tuning efforts including index optimization, query rewriting, and resource allocation adjustments.

•	Automated routine database maintenance tasks using PowerShell scripts, resulting in a 30% reduction in manual effort and freeing up time for strategic initiatives.


•	Led the successful migration of a mission-critical database from on-premises infrastructure to Google Cloud Platform and AWS, improving scalability and reducing infrastructure costs by 20%.

•	Implemented robust database security measures including role-based access control, data encryption, and regular security audits, ensuring compliance with industry regulations and protecting sensitive information from potential breaches.

•	Provided expert guidance and support during major incidents and system outages, minimizing downtime and restoring service within agreed-upon SLA parameters.

•	Mentored team members on database administration best practices, fostering professional growth and enhancing team capabilities.

•	Received recognition from management for outstanding performance and contributions to the overall stability and efficiency of the organization's database environment.
